Most roads in Sharpeville and Vanderbijlpark, south of Johannesburg were on Tuesday afternoon flooded amid heavy downpours associated with severe thunderstorms. The South African Weather Services earlier issued an alert for possible severe thunderstorms and as the day progressed, the alert was then escalated into a warning. The rainfall follows days of scorching hot weather conditions which gripped several parts of the country. The weather desk also said more rain was on the cards on Wednesday for Limpopo where chances are set to increase to between 60 and 80%. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.